              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">US banking reserves drop below $3 trillion</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">US banking system reserves dropped to the <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-06-01-2025-h2-3-lowest-level" target="_blank">lowest level</a> since October 2020. The $326 billion fall in reserves during the week ending Jan. 1 to $2.89 trillion marked the largest weekly decline since 2022. The drop came as banks made year-end balance sheet adjustments amidst ongoing quantitative tightening by the Federal Reserve. This has sparked a debate as many question how long the Fed can maintain QT without sparking liquidity issues reminiscent of 2019.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
